This paper proposes a method for disentangling epistemic and aleatoric uncertainties in deep reinforcement learning. The paper combines elements from distributional reinforcement learning and approximate Bayesian inference techniques with neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
